  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Become a Data Detective!\n\nEver wanted to track product prices, collect news headlines, or gather sports scores automatically? That's **web scraping** — and Python is perfect for it.\n\n### What You'll Learn\n- HTTP requests with the `requests` library\n- Parsing HTML with `BeautifulSoup`\n- Extracting specific data using CSS selectors\n- Saving scraped data to a file\n\n### How Web Scraping Works\n1. **Request** — Fetch the HTML of a webpage\n2. **Parse** — Turn raw HTML into a navigable tree\n3. **Select** — Find the exact elements you need\n4. **Extract** — Pull out text, links, or attributes\n\n> **Pro tip:** Always check a website's `robots.txt` and Terms of Service before scraping. Be ethical!"
  },
